            <div class="content-about-container-item">
                <div class="content-about-container-item-text">
                    <strong>Leaf Aid's Past, Present, and Future Activities</strong>
                </div>
                <div class="content-about-container-item-content">  
                    <p>Past Activities: Since its establishment, Leaf Aidhas carried out many practical activities and made a strong mark in the humanitarian field. To date, we have:</p>
                    <ul>
                        <li><strong><a href="/post/pempowering-futures-transforming-lives-through-educationp">Provided scholarships and educational opportunities</a></strong> to over 200,000 children in impoverished areas in Asia, Africa, and South America. We have built over 150 schools and hundreds of community libraries to help children have the conditions to study and develop.</li>
                        <li><strong><a href="/post/pstrongmillions-affected-by-severe-flooding-across-chad-nigeria-and-cameroonstrongp">Implemented community health campaigns</a></strong> in over 30 countries, supporting disease prevention and providing over 2 million doses of medicine and medical supplies to remote areas. Leaf Aidhas also built mobile health stations to provide timely support to people in emergency situations.</li>
                        <li><strong><a href="/post/psupporting-lives-in-crisis-providing-food-shelter-and-hope-to-over-500000-peoplep">Provided food and safe shelter</a></strong> to over 500,000 people affected by natural disasters and conflicts. We have built hundreds of temporary houses, community kitchens, and clean water systems in heavily affected areas.</li>
                    </ul>
                    <p>Ongoing Activities: Currently, Leaf Aid is continuing to implement many important projects to sustainably support the community:</p>
                    <ul>
                        <li><strong>>Global Clean Water Project :</strong> We are installing clean water systems in over 200 rural communities, helping people access safe water, improving health and living conditions.</li>
                        <li><strong>Vocational Training and Development Program:</strong> To help families have stable income sources, Leaf Aidis organizing vocational training courses and supporting small startups for over 10,000 women and youth. This program helps people become self-sufficient and improve their lives.</li>
                        <li><strong>Vaccination and Disease Prevention Campaign:</strong> Meeting the urgent needs in community healthcare, Leaf Aidis promoting vaccination campaigns, especially in areas vulnerable to diseases.</li>
                    </ul>
                    <p>Future Projects: In the coming years, Leaf Aidis committed to continuing to expand and develop new programs to create more positive and sustainable impacts:</p>
                    <ul>
                        <li><strong>Expanding Digital Education Program:</strong> With the goal of bridging the digital divide, we will provide digital classes, free devices, and internet access to schools and communities in remote areas, helping children and youth access technology.</li>
                        <li><strong>Building field hospitals in disaster and conflict hotspots:</strong> To respond to emergency situations, Leaf Aid will establish field hospitals and mobile medical teams, ready to support when disasters occur.</li>
                        <li><strong>Sustainable Housing Project:</strong> We will implement projects to build environmentally friendly, sustainable housing for disadvantaged communities, ensuring people have safe housing and contributing to environmental protection.</li>
                    </ul>
                    <p><b>Leaf Aid</b> always strives to ensure that every community contribution is used most effectively and creates real changes. Our journey does not stop at what has been achieved but will go further to spread hope to all those in need.</p>
